# Introduction

## Context of project

Quantified Student is a project where biometric data will be used to improve study performance. This will be similar to RunKeeper for studying. More data will be gathered to draw conclusions and create relationships. For instance, train departures, the weather and the season.

## Application

The application will consist of different parts, a data gathering application, an identity server, a front-end and back-end. The user does have a personal dashboard where he or she can see their personal performance of the day as well as other data, additionally the user can input some data.

## Non-functional Requirements

### Reliability

- --It must be possible to login to our system at least 95 percent of the time.
- --The system must have an uptime of at least 95 percent.
- --The system has both integration and unit tests to ensure that crucial classes will not break.
- --The system sends alerts by e-mail when errors occur on production.

### Performance

- --Logging in to the system must be possible within 2 seconds.
- --Retrieving data from the API must take no longer than 1 second.

### Security

- --All actions must be secured so unauthorized access is impossible.

### Scalability

- --All code is easy to read, well documented and easy to transfer to the next group

# Realization non-functional requirements

## Reliability

### It must be possible to login to our system at least 95 percent of the time

### The system must have an uptime of at least 95 percent

All errors that occur on our system will be logged to log files. The most important errors will be immediately emailed to the system admins. Because of that, errors can be solved very fast which should decrease downtime significantly.

## Performance

### Logging in to the system must be possible within 2 seconds

Performance is highly dependent on the network infrastructure and other network traffic. Logging in to the system and sending data to the API will run within the same network. Because it&#39;s in the same network one is not dependent of external network speeds. Since all communication for logging in to the server happens locally, it should take no longer than 2 seconds. If it takes longer, this is usually because the connection of the user is too slow.

### Retrieving data from the API must take no longer than 1 second

Such as logging in to the system, API calls are also highly dependent on the network infrastructure

## Security

### All actions must be secured so unauthorized access is impossible

All network traffic will be send with SSL encryption via HTTPS. Therefore, it will be not very easy to intercept network traffic by others.

Users must authenticate with their Fontys credentials. It is not possible to perform an API call when the user is not logged in. For security reasons, users should authenticate each time the browser is restarted.

## Scalability

### The application has a well-structured design that facilitates easy maintenance

The application makes use of dependency injection in the back end. Because of that, it is easier to migrate to a new database framework without interfering with other code.

In the front-end, all API calls will go via one JavaScript prototype (class), because of that it is very easy to switch to another API without having to change logic and GUI code.

### All code is easy to read and, well documented and easy to transfer to the next group

There are coding conventions set-upped which every programmer must follow. These coding conventions consist of obligatory code comments for each class and method as well as code conventions for naming of variables. There are also code review settings which will improve code quality and readability. Well-commented code will make it easier to transfer to the next group
